description:
Topsham, Maine was the scene of many significant events for the Advent believers, but for Ellen White it was the place that she lost her son, Henry White to death, at just 16 years old. This was the second child that the White family lost, and it was a particularly devastating blow to the family but God pulled them through.

To find out more about Henry White and the Howlands, read our extended article on our website.
